Job/Cronjob

Job Options

backoffLimit - Number of retries before failure
completions - Number of completed jobs you want
restartPolicy - Set it to Never
parallelism - Num. of pods running at the same time
activeDeadlineSeconds - Job will terminate if it STARTS but takes X secs to complete execution
Jobs - parallel,completions

Cron Options

startingDeadlineSeconds - CRONjob will terminate if takes X secs to start execution
Cron */2 * * * * Execute the job every two minutes

2 Create the logs in the main container. tail -f the logs in the sidecar

Ambassador: Used as a proxy container for the main app. The app code will be the same in prod,dev,qa,etc
Adapter: Formats ouput of the main app.

Labels

Create 3 pods and labels: for i in `seq 1 3`; do kubectl run nginx$i --image=nginx -l app=v1 ; done
Overwrite, change old value for app=v2: kubectl label pod nginx2 app=v2 --overwrite
Show all pods and highlight the ones labeled as "app": kubectl get pod -L app
Show only pods with label "app=v2": kubectl get po -l app=v2
Add new label "tier=web" to pods with label app=v1,v2: kubectl label pod -l "app in(v1,v2)" tier=web
Add annotation to pods with app=v2 label: kubectl annotate pod -l "app=v2" owner=marketing
Remove label "app" from all nginx pods: kubectl label pod nginx1 nginx2 nginx3 app-

Registry

1 Create: docker run -d -p 5000:5000 --restart=always --name my-registry registry:2
2 tag it: docker image tag my-image localhost:5000/my-image
3 Push: docker push localhost:5000/my-image
Check list images pushed: curl -X GET localhost:5000/v2/_catalog
